The assassin vine detects a creature within 20 feet
via tremorsense; Effect The assassin vine causes
vegetation within a 20-foot emanation to writhe for
1 round, turning this area into difficult terrain. When
a creature starts its turn in this area, it must attempt a
DC 20 Reflex save. On a failure, it takes a –10-foot
circumstance penalty to its Speeds until it
leaves the area, and on a critical
failure it is also immobilized for
1 round. A creature can
attempt to Escape to
remove these effects.
Assassin vines are immune
to Grasping Foliage.
Speed 5 feet
Melee [one-action] vine +12 (reach 10 feet), Damage
1d8+6 bludgeoning plus Grab
Constrict [one-action] 1d8+4 bludgeoning, DC 20
