Appendix
STYX PASSAGE FEES
Gliding with eerie ease along the
murky River Styx, thanadaemons
are only too happy to offer mortals
passage aboard their dilapidated
skiffs—for a price. Gold is typically
an acceptable payment for a
thanadaemon’s services, though these
fiends are well-known for altering the
details of arrangements after the fact,
and may just as likely demand a favor
or some esoteric good, such as a soul
gem, instead of coin.
