Speed 20 feet, burrow 20 feet; earth glide
Melee [one-action] jaws +10, Damage 1d8+6 piercing
Earth Glide A living boulder can Burrow through earthen matter, including rock.
When it does so, it moves at its full burrow Speed, leaving no tunnels or signs
of its passing.
Rolling Charge[two-actions] The living boulder Strides twice, and can then make a Strike
with its jaws. This jaws Strike gains Knockdown.
