MEPHIT NAMES
Perhaps because they’re so often
compelled into service by mortal
conjurers and more powerful
elementals, mephits tend to adopt long
names peppered with self-proclaimed
titles and imagined or exaggerated
accomplishments to alleviate their
feelings of inadequacy. Some examples
of mephit names follow.
• Anothoraxia, Lurker in Dark Places,
the Tragic Hero, One Against All
• Silothiscil the Embittered, Rimelord
of the Eternal Chill, Lord of Icicles
• Oglophax, Prince of Pungency, the
Viscous One, the Forever Stain
• Zarnozath the Magnificent, First
of His Name, Boiler of Kettles, the
Teapot Terror
