water) The grodair transforms all soil,
sand, or similar sediment in a 10‑foot
emanation into mud for 1 round. This mud is
difficult terrain for creatures other than grodairs.
Organ of Endless Water [one-action] (conjuration, manipulate, primal,
water) The grodair causes water to pour from a magical sac on its
spine, either a stream of water at a rate of 1 gallon per round, or a fountain in a
5‑foot‑long stream at a rate of 5 gallons per round. It can stop the flow of water as
a single action. 
