action and throws it as a ranged Strike.
OREAD
Elemental earth laces through the bones of oreads, who appear similar to stone
statues of their mortal ancestry, with delicate crystals in place of hair, fur, or
scales. Oreads are stoic and slow to plan but are of steadfast resolve and
unwavering in their convictions.
The typical oread cherishes quiet seclusion. Yet as they age, many
oreads find themselves inexplicably drawn to some far-flung location 
