in the previous round; Effect The quickling becomes invisible until it uses an attack,
manipulate, or move action. The quickling can’t use Fade from View again for 1d4 rounds.
Sneak Attack The quickling’s Strikes deal an extra 1d6 precision damage to
flat-footed creatures.
Supernatural Speed The quickling’s speed, combined with nearly instantaneous
acceleration and deceleration, enables them to move in astonishing ways. As
long as they have a firm surface to travel across, they can Stride their full
movement vertically or horizontally. They can even run across unstable
surfaces, such as water, in the same way,
although dangerous surfaces (acid, lava,
etc.) harm them as normal. They must
end their movement on a horizontal surface
capable of bearing their weight or else they fall.
