WERETIGER
These ferocious werecreatures stalk prey with the cunning and skill of a true
apex predator. Weretigers typically view all life as a potential meal.
Powerful nocturnal hunters with excellent senses that help them
ambush prey, weretigers are adaptable to an extreme range of
environments. However, weretigers living in densely populated
cities (potentially as courtesans, assassins, or guild leaders)
often struggle to suppress their killer instincts, becoming
overwhelmed by the urge to hunt. They prefer to wear loosefitting clothing and rely on their claws and jaws in a fight.
